abstract: Former Buffalo Bills center Kent Hull dies at age 50 from unknown cause.
snippet: Kent Hull, who served as the center for the Hall of Fame quarterback Jim Kelly during the Buffalo Bills’ A.F.C. title years in the early 1990s, died.
lead_paragraph: Kent Hull, who served as the center for the Hall of Fame quarterback Jim Kelly during the Buffalo Bills’ A.F.C. title years in the early 1990s, died.
